{
  "stem": "27509.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But-- and in time, in time, although he would never compromise on these convictions in a religious sense, and so on, he understood.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He was sufficiently progressive to understand that he can't hold the tide of time back.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And he graciously-- outwardly, at least, if not inwardly-- gave in, sometimes with a smile and sometimes with a concerned brow that, my god, what are the times doing to me-- this sort of expression.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But just the same, it was a very warm, warm relationship, although there was no hugging, and there was no kissing, and there was no-- not sort of this outward manifestation of a dilettante sort of a attachment.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But it was deep, inward, tangible, yet undemonstrative, undemonstrative.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, it had the impact on my education because, in a sense, his insistence on giving me a Jewish education, to start with, gave me the grounding for everything else that I learned afterwards, because I-- by the time I have studied at the different schools-- before I get-- came to the gymnasium, I had so much, so much Hebrew knowledge and Talmudic knowledge, already attained, that I remember one of the first lessons, that I came to the class.",
      "word_count": 80
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the teacher, in Hebrew, which was a very brilliant teacher, discussed a certain item.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he wanted some sort of a-- a form of expression to meet a certain concept.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I lifted my finger up, and I quoted to him from [NON-ENGLISH], not from the Talmud text, but from [NON-ENGLISH], in Aramaic, which was just, just exactly what he looked for.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The man looked at me, and he said, yes.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He said, that's it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He said, that's it.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
